sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuthProxy as oauth-proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Dashboard as Ray Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant Operator as CodeFlare Operator
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant InitContainer as mTLS Init Container
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Pod<br/>10001/TCP mTLS
    participant RayWorker as Ray Worker Pod<br/>mTLS
    participant RayClient as Ray Client

    Note over User,Dashboard: Flow 1: Ray Dashboard OAuth Access (OpenShift)
    User->>Router: GET ray-dashboard-{name}<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    Router->>OAuthProxy: Forward (TLS Reencrypt)<br/>HTTPS/8443
    OAuthProxy->>OAuthServer: OAuth redirect flow<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    OAuthServer-->>OAuthProxy: Auth token
    OAuthProxy->>Dashboard: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8265 (localhost)
    Dashboard-->>OAuthProxy: Dashboard response
    OAuthProxy-->>Router: HTTPS response
    Router-->>User: Dashboard HTML

    Note over Operator,RayWorker: Flow 2: mTLS Certificate Provisioning
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch RayCluster CRs<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: RayCluster event
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create ca-secret-{cluster}<br/>RSA 2048-bit CA cert
    Note over InitContainer: Pod starts with init containers
    InitContainer->>InitContainer: Read CA from Secret volume
    InitContainer->>InitContainer: Generate node cert<br/>(openssl, signed by cluster CA)
    InitContainer->>InitContainer: Write cert to EmptyDir

    Note over RayHead,RayWorker: Flow 2 (cont): Ray Inter-node mTLS
    RayHead->>RayWorker: Ray GCS/Object Store<br/>10001/TCP, mTLS (cluster CA)
    RayWorker->>RayHead: Ray protocol<br/>mTLS (cluster CA)

    Note over RayClient,RayHead: Flow 3: Ray Client Connection (OpenShift)
    RayClient->>Router: Connect to rayclient-{name}<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS passthrough
    Router->>RayHead: Forward (TLS Passthrough)<br/>10001/TCP, mTLS
    RayHead-->>Router: Ray response<br/>mTLS (cluster CA)
    Router-->>RayClient: Response
